column5:
Merge pull request #52 from fatman-/patch-1

Fix code typo in 'Function' example in README.md

Merge pull request #48 from kvu787/patch-1

fix typo
Add a link to vim syntax highlighting

Fix for installation issues

drop weird dependency camlp4lib
Implement exists() for Winbat and add unit test
Not ignore string case in if statement (winbat)
Print SemanticError in command line tool
File existence test in a if statement (bash)

Not split string comparison expression in a stand-alone assignment statement

In order to reduce temporary variables

Merge pull request #15 from Nixola/patch-1

Update README.md

Merge pull request #8 from mirez/master

Spelling, grammar changes
Add Errors to handle all exceptions

Update README

Add built-in functions and tune other texts

Use `rem` instead of `::` for comments (winbat)

`rem` is more compatible and less ambiguous than `::`
Check if return value is a list literal
Check if qualified `global` is defined in a function
Rename extension names of all test files to .batsh.

Fix newline in a string literal (winbat).

Issue #2
Sanitize files and fix external interface.

Deal with argument with space by passing name of variables (winbat).

Issue #4

Deal with argument with space by quoting all variables (bash).

Reference: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/1983048/passing-a-string-with-spaces-as-a-function-argument-in-bash
Read version and description from batsh.ocp.
Update makefile to enable test result update.

Use ocamlyacc for compatibility.

Stop using menhir.

Support return value of external command (winbat).

Now statements like `a=dir();` are available.
Split string literal from call parameters if space is found.

Depend on Core_kernel instead.

Core_kernel is the platform-dependent part of Core library, which might be portable.
Now batsh library depend on Core_kernel.
Only main.ml and test.ml still depend on Core.
Escape caret specially if exclamation mark is observed (winbat).
Rename extension name of all tests.
Not split string comparison expression from if statement.
Stop printing redundant parentheses of arithmetic expressions (bash).

Add unit tests for code result.

Add script for updating unit test results.
Remove ambiguous subexpression parameter of split_expression.

Rename Batsh_transform to Bash_transform.

Remove `ast` subcommand.
Print abstract syntax tree of Winbat.

Split unit tests.

Remove expr.c and add string.c and command.c.

Fix arithmetic comparisons (winbat).

Compile arithmetic comparisons to if statements.
Split subexpressions of arithmetic comparisions.

Fix exclamation mark escape (winbat).

! must be represented as ^^!.
But it is not interpreted correctly by wine.

Fix recursion (winbat).

Add _%~2 to suffix of return value in call statement inside function scope.

Add parameters = varstrings list (winbat).

Stop concatenating multiple parameters into one in function call.

Print the return value if it is not assigned to a variable (winbat).

This would be consistent with bash.
Behavior of printing an undefined variable is undefined.

Fix print() (winbat).

Do not print whitespace at the beginning by using `Cont as a marker.

Raw statement support.

Add `bash()` and `batch()`.
Add `readdir()`.
Allocate a label in symbol table when translating while loop.
Symbol_table is no longer a submodule of Parser.
Compile string comparison in an assignment (winbat).
Remove ambiguous `subexpression` in split_expression of winbat.
Raise exception instead of quit when error parsing.

Print code to buffer instead of out_channel.

Out_channel is not in-memory.

Reorganize modules and package.

Rename batsh_lib to batsh.
Rename Parser to Parser_yacc.
Rename Batsh to Parser.
Deal with return value in batch.

Increase frame pointer in function call.

When call is found int batch, see if it is in function scope. If so then increase frame pointer by 1.
Also fix a bug, now parameters are considered as local variables.
Deal with global variable in batch functions.

Use List.stable_sort to sort functions.

Fix some style problems.
Also prepend empty statement to functions and program.

New Makefile.

Cache binary of setup.ml therefore makes incremental build faster.

Replace lots of list concatenations with Dlist.

In order to improve efficiency, Dlist is introduced, by using which all
list concatencations are reduced to O(1) complexity rather than O(N).
Rename package name to avoid conflict

Translate function in Winbat

Return value is not supported yet

Winbat: While statement

Escape parentheses with ^
Fix print and println

If and else for Winbat

Split expressions alone in Winbat
Use polymorphic variants to simpilfy Winbat_ast
String concatenation and assignment in Winbat
Not split arithmetic expressions in bash

Translate arithmetic expressions in Winbat

Block is flattened
Modulo operator is escaped

Expand Winbat functions

Force EnableDelayedExpansion
Print bare and not bare variable
Compile arithmetic and call into Winbat

Implement Batsh_transform to split complex expressions into assignments

extract_temporary is moved into Batsh_transform
Remove redundant Parenthsis type
Split StrBinary into Concat and StrCompare

Function "call"

Change first parameter of Bash_ast.Command to expression

Implement bash function expansion

print -> echo -ne
println -> echo -e

Sexp serialization support of Batsh_ast

Rename Batsh_ast.asttype to Batsh_ast.t
Add Batsh.create_from_file
Add subcommands for main
Allow parse_and_print_error to specify out channel

Fix order of test statement

Add test for if statement.

Handle string comparison

Add StrTemp.
Add ArithUnary.

Introduce string equal (==) and arithmetic equal (===)

Unify ++ == != to StrBinary.

Extract string expression from arithmetic expression

Replace them with temporary variables generated by symbol table.
Unify binary expressions to ArithBinary.
Remove bash "let" statement.
Fix typo and add syntax examples
Update function unit test: global variable
Only print `-` in an empty block
Store variables separately in symbol table
Fix bug of generating assignments in bash
Print single statement after if/while correctly
Print bash block and reduce redundant line ending in print_statements

Make new type leftvalue consisting of Identifier and ListAccess
Print list literal
Extract common output functions to Formatutil
Manually force to compare with 1 in if expression
Rename concatenation to expression in bash.ml
Add a parameter to command line
Fix shift/reduce conflict of if then else
